REHI Color Palette — Usage Reference
Hex	Color Name	Role	Used For
#EEE6DD	Warm Cream	Background	Page backgrounds, section fills
#232220	Charcoal Black	Foreground	Body text, headings on light backgrounds
#31321F	Dark Olive	Primary	Buttons, hero banners, CTA sections, active nav, logo accent
#D3D0BC	Warm Tan	Muted	Alternating section backgrounds (stats bands, timeline rows)
#929F9D	Muted Sage	Muted Text	Subtitles, descriptions, secondary labels, placeholder text


                        Supporting Derived Values
Role	            Value	                 Notes
Card	            Near-white #F9F6F3	    Cards, form panels — slightly lighter than cream so they lift off the background
Border	            Tan-mid #B8B4A0	    Card borders, dividers, input edges
Primary Foreground	Cream #EEE6DD	        Text/icons placed on top of dark olive buttons and hero banners
Ring / Focus	    Dark Olive #31321F	    Input focus rings, keyboard navigation outlines
Destructive	        Soft Red #D94F4F	    Error states, delete actions


Quick Rule of Thumb
Dark olive  (#31321F)  →  any interactive element that needs to be clicked
Cream       (#EEE6DD)  →  any text or background sitting on dark olive
Charcoal    (#232220)  →  any body text on cream/card/tan backgrounds
Warm Tan    (#D3D0BC)  →  section backgrounds to break up cream monotony
Muted Sage  (#929F9D)  →  anything secondary — captions, labels, subtitles